      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p030_s0003",
      "text": "3.2.137",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        57.65,
        129.33,
        68.76
      ],
      "block_index": 3,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p030_s0004",
      "text": "Worldwide_Name: ",
      "bbox": [
        139.33,
        57.65,
        228.73,
        68.76
      ],
      "block_index": 3,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p030_s0005",
      "text": "A Name_Identifier that is worldwide unique (see FC-FS-2).",
      "bbox": [
        228.72,
        57.65,
        487.59,
        68.76
      ],
      "block_index": 3,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 2
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p030_s0006",
      "text": "3.3",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        82.97,
        109.88,
        94.08
      ],
      "block_index": 4,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p030_s0007",
      "text": "Editorial Conventions",
      "bbox": [
        119.88,
        82.97,
        223.2,
        94.08
      ],
      "block_index": 4,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p030_s0008",
      "text": "In this standard, a number of conditions, mechanisms, sequences, parameters, events, states or oth-",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        106.97,
        540.04,
        118.08
      ],
      "block_index": 5,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p030_s0009",
      "text": "er terms are printed with the first letter of each word in uppercase and the rest lowercase.  This indi-",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        118.97,
        540.23,
        130.08
      ],
      "block_index": 5,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p030_s0010",
      "text": "cates that they have a special meaning in the context of this standard.  The meaning is either",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        130.97,
        540.03,
        142.08
      ],
      "block_index": 5,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p030_s0011",
      "text": "described in the relevant text, in the glossary of this standard, or in a referenced standard (e.g., Ex-",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        142.96,
        540.03,
        154.08
      ],
      "block_index": 5,
      "line_index": 4,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p030_s0012",
      "text": "change and Class).  Any use of these terms in lowercase indicates that the words have the normal",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        154.96,
        540.0,
        166.08
      ],
      "block_index": 5,
      "line_index": 5,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p030_s0013",
      "text": "technical English meanings.",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        166.96,
        219.88,
        178.08
      ],
      "block_index": 5,
      "line_index": 6,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p030_s0014",
      "text": "Lists sequenced by letters (e.g., a-red, b-blue, c-green) show no priority relationship between the list-",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        190.96,
        540.0,
        202.08
      ],
      "block_index": 6,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p030_s0015",
      "text": "ed items. Numbered lists (e.g., 1-red, 2-blue, 3-green) show a priority ordering between the listed",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        202.96,
        539.96,
        214.08
      ],
      "block_index": 6,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p030_s0016",
      "text": "items.",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        214.96,
        122.65,
        226.08
      ],
      "block_index": 6,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p030_s0017",
      "text": "The ISO convention of numbering is used (i.e., the thousands and higher multiples are separated by",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        238.96,
        540.03,
        250.08
      ],
      "block_index": 7,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p030_s0018",
      "text": "a space and a comma is used as the decimal point.)   A comparison of the American and ISO con-",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        250.96,
        539.9,
        262.08
      ],
      "block_index": 7,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p030_s0019",
      "text": "ventions are shown in table 1. ",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        262.96,
        230.97,
        274.08
      ],
      "block_index": 7,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p030_s0020",
      "text": "In case of any conflict between figure, table, and text, the text, then tables, and finally figures take",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        406.96,
        539.91,
        418.08
      ],
      "block_index": 8,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p030_s0021",
      "text": "precedence. Exceptions to this convention are indicated in the appropriate sections.",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        418.96,
        466.01,
        430.08
      ],
      "block_index": 8,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p030_s0022",
      "text": "In all of the figures, tables, and text of this document, the most significant bit of a binary quantity is",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        442.96,
        540.09,
        454.08
      ],
      "block_index": 9,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p030_s0023",
      "text": "shown on the left side. Exceptions to this convention are indicated in the appropriate sections.",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        454.96,
        510.43,
        466.08
      ],
      "block_index": 9,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p030_s0024",
      "text": "If a field or a control bit in a frame is specified as reserved, the entity that sends the frame shall set",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        478.96,
        539.87,
        490.08
      ],
      "block_index": 10,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p030_s0025",
      "text": "the field or control bit to zero, and the entity that receives the frame shall not check that field or con-",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        490.96,
        540.04,
        502.08
      ],
      "block_index": 10,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p030_s0026",
      "text": "trol bit.",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        502.96,
        125.94,
        514.08
      ],
      "block_index": 10,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p030_s0027",
      "text": "When the value of the bit or field is not relevant, x or xx appears in place of a specific value.",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        526.96,
        500.45,
        538.08
      ],
      "block_index": 11,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p030_s0028",
      "text": "Unless stated otherwise: numbers that are not immediately followed by lower-case b or h are decimal",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        550.96,
        540.03,
        562.08
      ],
      "block_index": 12,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p030_s0029",
      "text": "values; numbers immediately followed by lower-case b (xxb) are binary values; and numbers or up-",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        562.96,
        540.06,
        574.08
      ],
      "block_index": 12,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p030_s0030",
      "text": "per case letters immediately followed by lower-case h (xxh) are hexadecimal values.",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        574.96,
        468.09,
        586.08
      ],
      "block_index": 12,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p030_s0031",
      "text": "3.4",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        598.96,
        109.88,
        610.08
      ],
      "block_index": 13,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p030_s0032",
      "text": "State Machine notation",
      "bbox": [
        119.88,
        598.96,
        229.3,
        610.08
      ],
      "block_index": 13,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p030_s0033",
      "text": "State machines in this standard should use the style shown in figure 1.",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        622.96,
        407.62,
        634.07
      ],
      "block_index": 14,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p030_s0034",
      "text": "These state machines make three assumptions:",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        647.02,
        308.15,
        658.14
      ],
      "block_index": 15,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p030_s0035",
      "text": "a) Time elapses only within discrete states.",
      "bbox": [
        106.02,
        671.02,
        301.26,
        682.13
      ],
      "block_index": 16,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
